Standard and Poor's Corp said itdowngraded 160 mln dlrs of debt of Norstar Bancorp.    Cut were the company's senior debt to AA-minus from AA,subordinated debt to A-plus from AA-minus and preferred stockto A from A-plus. S/P affirmed its A-1-plus commercial paper.    The downgrade reflected a modest increase in Norstar's riskprofile, combined with lower financial performance. Norstar'srecent purchase of the 1.2 billion dlr Syracuse Savings Bankwill require substantial management and financial resources tobring the unit's performance in line with the bank's otheroperations, the agency said. Reuter&#3;